TRACY TOWING LINE, Inc., as Owner of THE Steam Tug O’BRIEN SISTERS, Libelant-Appellant, v. THE Steam Tug MADISON, Her Engines, etc., The Delaware, Lackawanna & Western Railroad Company, Claimant-Appellee. No. 296. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. March 13, 1933. Macklin, Brown, Lenahan & Speer, of New York City (Horace L. Cheyney, of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. John E. Morrissey, of New York City, for appellee.

Before MANTON, SWAN, and CHASE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Decree affirmed.
